args: If you are bored, I'm happy to\nfind something for you to do.
I dunno. Somehow I just haven't felt\nvery motivated since we got back.
You went from battling our enemies \nto battling a mountain of paperwork.
Well, I'll be sure to avoid\npromotions at all cost.
Honestly, why are you even here?\nYou were granted leave days ago.
Guess I couldn't bear to leave your side.
Easy, there! Just a joke, is all.\nI'll get out of your hair if you want.
You saved my life. I won't forget it.\nThank you.
Hey, whoa. This isn't like you at all.
Frankly, I didn't save you so much as\nnearly ruin everything and then figure\nout how to pull my butt out of the fire.
Enough with the false modesty.\nWithout your little surprise attack,\nI wouldn't be standing here today.
So if you won't use your leave,\nI'll have to reward you myself.\nAnything strike your fancy?
Oh, nothing in particular. Except,\nwell...maybe a kiss from a lady?
You are out of line, soldier!
...At least, that's what I'd normally say.
Whoa, wait! Is this happening?!\n'Cause I was mostly—
Do you want your reward or not?
Y-yes, ma'am! Eyes are closed, ma'am!
(I can't believe this is going to happen...\nI wasn't even serious!)
...Ma'am? Is that sound what I think it is?
Precisely. Your reward is to\nassist with all of this.
Separate out the important documents so\nI can look them over. For everything else,\njust forge my signature.
You let me worry about that.\nNow get to work before you\nlose the sun!
Ugh. I'm halfway through, but there's\nstill so much paperwork to go.
Do not stay your hand, Joachim.
My shoulders are a bit stiff.
One military-grade back rub, coming up.
Black as night, and strong enough\nto float a gold piece on the top.
Er, I think I have some leftover\nsalami in my rations?
Unacceptable! I need a hot meal\nin order to maintain my focus!
Fine, I'll throw something together.\nHow's deer soup sound?
*siiigh* Me too. Somehow.\n'Course, my fingers might pop off\nand run away at any moment...
Hmm. This was most efficient.\nWe'll use this method for all\npaperwork going forward.
Uh, does that mean I'll be the one\nin the barrel every time?
Of course! Now let's get going.
You have a dog to walk.\nIt's part of your daily routine, yes?
I'll join you—unless you'd prefer I didn't?
Good girl! Your coat is beautiful!
I see you're taking good care of her.
She is your sister's dog, after all.
It has been seven years, Joachim.\nSurely she would want you to\nmove on after all this time.
Please, ma'am. Just...stop.\nI don't want to talk about it.
You're not family, so it\ndoesn't concern you.
No, don't apologize.\nI'm the one at fault.
Er, is that everyone's favorite messenger?
Commander Kirsty!\nI have urgent orders from HQ!
Well, this is sooner than expected.\nHand them over.
...Yes, I see. As expected, what happened\nat the border was only the beginning.
Muster the troops immediately.\nLeave will have to be cut short.\nWe have much to accomplish.
